meta.message: Potential causes identified based on user profile and health concern.

potential_causes.explanation_localized: Not drinking enough water can lead to headaches, especially in children, due to dehydration.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Establish a consistent bedtime routine and ensure adequate sleep.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Poor sleep quality or insufficient sleep commonly causes headaches in children.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Limit daily screen time and ensure regular breaks.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Excessive screen use can cause eye strain and headaches in children.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Create a calm environment and encourage relaxation activities.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Emotional stress and anxiety can manifest physically as headaches in children.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Encourage good posture and ergonomic habits.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Poor posture, especially during homework or screen time, can lead to tension headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Ensure a balanced diet and regular meal times.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Certain dietary choices or irregular eating patterns may contribute to headaches.

potential_causes.suggestion_localized: Create a quiet, well-ventilated, and comfortable sleeping environment.
potential_causes.explanation_localized: Environmental noise, lighting, or air quality issues can trigger headaches in sensitive children.
